<body>
  <h1>Login Page</h1>
  
  <form action="Servlet1" method="post">
    <label for="username">Username:</label>
    <input type="text" id="username" name="username" required><br><br>
        
    <label for="password">Password:</label>
    <input type="password" id="password" name="password" required><br><br>
        
    <input type="submit" value="Login">
    <input type="reset" value="Reset">
  </form>

	<p>This is a simple login page. Enter your username and password to
		login. When you click the "Login" button, the data will be sent to the
		Servlet1 servlet. Servlet1 will store the username and password in the
		session and redirect to another form page. On the second form page
		(FetchUserDetails.html), you can enter additional details and submit
		the form. The data from the second form will be sent to the Servlet2
		servlet, which will store the additional values in the session and
		redirect to the summary page (Summary.html). The summary page will
		display all the entered details, including the username, password,
		additional details, and a thank you message.</p>
</body>
